description:
What’s significant about COP27, the UN’s yearly climate change conference happening at Sinai? Why has climate justice become a rallying point for world religions? Is there a dark side to religious environmentalism? 

This video looks at how Biblical stories are being used to bring religion and ecology together and to promote the climate action agenda. Are carbon neutrality and climate justice actions real solutions to the world’s problems? Or are they tools for coercion? What does the Bible say about these things? Find out in this episode with MacKenzie Drebit and Matthew Schanche.
